text.section:
A captive insurer shall be formed as a:
Stock insurer with its capital divided into shares and held by the stockholders;
Mutual insurer without capital stock in accordance with Subtitle 24 of this chapter;
Reciprocal insurer in accordance with Subtitle 27 of this chapter;
Limited liability company pursuant to KRS Chapter 275;
Business corporation pursuant to KRS Chapter 271B;
Nonstock, nonprofit corporation pursuant to KRS Chapter 273; or
Partnership, limited partnership, statutory business trust, or other legal person or entity other than a natural person in his or her individual capacity, with the approval of the commissioner upon a showing of demonstrated need.
